WEBVTT

00:00.386 --> 00:03.430
Hey River Valley, this weekend we're gonna hear from Scott Hagen.

00:03.770 --> 00:07.555
He's president of North Central University and he's also a friend of mine.

00:07.835 --> 00:12.941
And I asked him to preach this weekend because we're remembering 9-11 with the 20th anniversary.

00:13.282 --> 00:17.206
And he just had a new book come out on Call Heroes that he published with Tyndale.

00:17.226 --> 00:18.328
They asked him to do this.

00:18.368 --> 00:26.898
They said, can you just honor those people all the way back to the first responders that ran into the fire and went into the buildings 20 years ago?

00:26.978 --> 00:37.248
And then honor the people that over the last year and a half have been on the front lines, those heroes, those doctors, nurses, people that ran into the trouble and didn't run away.

00:37.608 --> 00:41.992
And so I asked them to speak on that this weekend and to be able to sell the book.

00:42.032 --> 00:43.333
So here's the idea with the book.

00:43.373 --> 00:51.581
You can buy one, give it to a doctor, a nurse, a firefighter, a police officer, anyone that was that on-call hero that you just want to bless.

00:51.641 --> 00:54.984
It's $15, you can get the book for them and sew it into their life.

00:55.044 --> 00:56.786
It's a great opportunity to say,

00:57.410 --> 00:58.271
You made a difference.

00:58.592 --> 01:01.216
We noticed and we care and we appreciate you.

01:01.336 --> 01:05.161
So we're going to jump into his message right now and he's going to be speaking on this.

01:05.261 --> 01:09.367
And so I pray you'll open up your heart to the message that Scott Hagen is bringing right now.

01:09.808 --> 01:12.191
I travel pretty much three weekends a month.

01:12.211 --> 01:17.820
Sometimes all four weekends I'm out preaching most of the time in churches with multiple services like this.

01:18.280 --> 01:20.303
And I have found this to be absolutely true.

01:21.044 --> 01:25.010
If there's a Saturday night and two Sunday morning, I'm telling you straight up.

01:25.858 --> 01:30.467
The most spiritual people in the church come to the last service on Sunday.

01:30.707 --> 01:32.451
It's absolutely proven true.

01:33.312 --> 01:34.494
And I'll show you why.

01:34.535 --> 01:36.458
The Saturday night folks, we love Saturday night.

01:36.879 --> 01:38.823
But come on, man, they're checking it off the list.

01:38.843 --> 01:40.085
They're just getting it through.

01:40.125 --> 01:43.932
The early service, 9 o'clock folks, I love them.

01:43.952 --> 01:46.898
But they're on their way to lunch or they have bad

01:46.978 --> 01:49.721
home technology and don't know how to tape the Vikings game.

01:50.082 --> 01:52.985
I don't know what their issue is, but you folks have been upset.

01:53.005 --> 01:58.712
It's about 4.35 a.m. this morning praying at least two to three hours prior to coming in the auditorium.

01:59.372 --> 02:03.838
The 11 o'clock crowd, most spiritual people in America, give yourself a round of applause.

02:04.679 --> 02:05.700
I know where you're coming from.

02:08.223 --> 02:10.045
Pastor Rob is accurate.

02:10.065 --> 02:11.887
We have a fantastic relationship.

02:12.468 --> 02:14.450
Rob is a great friend.

02:14.562 --> 02:18.830
during this last year because we're both from Minneapolis and we traveled around the nation.

02:19.311 --> 02:25.343
We pretty much found ourselves in the center of national conversations with leaders about what it's like in Minneapolis.

02:25.864 --> 02:36.786
When we went through really the tip of the spear about a year and a half ago, Rob was right there with me and Becca, they supported the school, came to the events,

02:36.898 --> 02:38.780
and just were right next to us.

02:38.860 --> 02:44.566
He serves as a national executive press for the Assembly of the Assembly of God, which makes him a board member at North Central.

02:44.606 --> 02:50.692
But I believe your pastor, we all know he's extraordinarily gifted, one of a kind in the world.

02:51.733 --> 03:02.084
But I think the trait I saw in Rob Ketterling this last year was a level of courage in Rob that was pastoral, but prophetic.

03:02.104 --> 03:03.986
And I think that's what I most

03:04.098 --> 03:15.159
admire in Rob Ketterling is he's a super nice, fantastic leader, but there is a fire and a steel cord of courage inside Rob Ketterling that is undeniable.

03:15.199 --> 03:19.807
You have a great pastor, great leader, very grateful to God, very grateful to God.

03:22.012 --> 03:27.602
To join to be here with my bride of 39 years, we've been married and we were married

03:27.682 --> 03:29.904
We're a few days apart in age.

03:30.085 --> 03:31.967
She's got me, like, by six weeks.

03:32.267 --> 03:35.771
I'm turning 59 in about a week, then we'll both be turning 60 next year.

03:36.712 --> 03:38.173
And we'll be in our 40th year of marriage.

03:38.193 --> 03:39.254
We just celebrated 39.

03:40.135 --> 03:41.477
But my beautiful bride is here.

03:41.537 --> 03:42.958
Karen, would you stand real quick here?

03:43.018 --> 03:44.120
Third service right there.

03:44.200 --> 03:44.600
That's her.

03:45.261 --> 03:49.125
But here's my favorite photo of Karen.

03:49.165 --> 03:51.187
My favorite picture of Karen is on the screen.

03:51.207 --> 03:53.810
1966 Easter Sunday.

03:53.922 --> 03:56.265
I love the matching purse, the matching dress.

03:56.445 --> 04:01.471
I love the little page boy haircut, the bret or whatever that thing is in her hair right there.

04:02.272 --> 04:05.937
I love the little feminine bent wrist, but it's the gleam in her eye.

04:05.977 --> 04:12.105
It's that look, it's that twinkle, that sparkle, that gleam in her eye.

04:12.185 --> 04:16.510
Very few things on this earth give a woman that gleam.

04:17.291 --> 04:21.517
I think that woman only gets that gleam in the eye maybe once in her lifetime.

04:21.537 --> 04:22.578
I think God

04:22.818 --> 04:27.205
blessed Karen by showing her future way ahead of time.

04:27.245 --> 04:28.667
I think this is what Karen saw.

04:28.707 --> 04:39.443
It's a pretty energetic laugh for 11 o'clock after I complimented your spirituality.

04:39.704 --> 04:42.448
I got my twisty velvet pants on there.

04:42.508 --> 04:47.356
My little patent leather prison shoes right there.

04:48.838 --> 04:51.602
My brother's got his prison outfit on next to me right there.

04:52.738 --> 05:00.427
My dad, he worked in the timber industry, the lumber industry for warehouser, and his job was to go into the mountains in the northwest and cut the trees down.

05:00.447 --> 05:06.213
He had a humongous chainsaw, and it was his pride and joy, and it was like his Harley Davidson.

05:06.233 --> 05:09.177
I used to smell the oil of that chainsaw every night.

05:09.217 --> 05:12.861
I couldn't touch it, but my dad was very gifted with the chainsaw.

05:12.881 --> 05:15.884
He also was responsible for giving me my haircuts.

05:16.465 --> 05:20.850
And I think my dad somehow combined his love of the chainsaw and his

05:21.474 --> 05:22.856
was possible to cut my hair.

05:23.897 --> 05:28.123
But I told our students in North Central, you put a pair of skinny jeans on that guy.

05:28.183 --> 05:32.068
That is a modern worship leader haircut in America right now.

05:32.088 --> 05:35.293
It's way out over my ski tips with that hairdo right there.

05:37.015 --> 05:37.876
No, it's great.

05:37.896 --> 05:41.741
We end up having 10 beautiful grandkids and the Lord has blessed our family.

05:41.782 --> 05:46.668
I just want to say too that just a big thank you on behalf of the university.

05:47.549 --> 05:50.994
I found out yesterday, over the last 23 years,

05:51.298 --> 05:52.219
River Valley Church.

05:52.279 --> 05:55.344
This isn't the personal giving which has been significant.

05:55.364 --> 06:14.650
This is just church giving through Apple Valley and all the campuses, but primarily this Apple Valley campus has given $1,229,000, $229,700 to North Central University for scholarships and building programs.

06:14.730 --> 06:20.658
That is a standalone generosity toward the university.

06:20.770 --> 06:23.055
Many of your staff have come through North Central.

06:23.075 --> 06:25.039
We want to continue that powerful relationship.

06:25.079 --> 06:29.227
Many of the missionaries that you're sending around the world come out of that great institution.

06:29.648 --> 06:38.546
But whether you want to be a biologist, a biblical biologist, a scripture first scientist, a top educator, a business leader, worship leader,

06:38.626 --> 06:45.414
Pastor, youth pastor, North Central I think is at the top of its game and God has watched over this great school.

06:45.434 --> 06:51.182
I just want to say thank you to River Valley for keeping North Central strong and vibrant into the future.

06:51.242 --> 06:52.043
God has been good.

06:52.083 --> 06:55.026
Can we just say thank you Lord for His keeping power.

06:55.126 --> 06:55.447
Amen.

06:57.189 --> 07:01.054
This morning I want you to take your Bibles or watch on the screen Joshua chapter 14.

07:01.234 --> 07:04.498
I want to preach this morning for a few minutes.

07:04.962 --> 07:09.849
on what does a last days first responder actually look like?

07:10.891 --> 07:25.793
I'm not just trying to be pop culture-ish and play off this weekend or the book, but I want to show you a portrait of a powerful first responder in the Old Testament that really looks like what the last days ought to be.

07:26.734 --> 07:32.082
I don't think the story in Joshua 14 has ever meant more to my life than it means right now.

07:32.866 --> 07:45.018
Much of what I see going on in the conversation between Caleb and Joshua and the kind of leader Joshua was, I am longing for that in my own life.

07:45.438 --> 07:46.939
Let's read together Joshua 14.

07:47.440 --> 07:50.183
This is a conversation between Joshua and Caleb.

07:50.203 --> 07:52.685
Now these guys are in their 80s.

07:53.686 --> 08:02.194
This story, those 45 years in the making, it's a conversation that started when they were 40 and now they're in their mid 80s.

08:02.338 --> 08:08.904
They're closing escrow, literally handing the keys out to the Promised Land.

08:08.924 --> 08:12.768
Something that Caleb has been anticipating for 45 years.

08:14.089 --> 08:19.935
And he says to Joshua, I've been waiting for this day for a long time and here it is.

08:21.296 --> 08:25.500
No matter what, my collective world around me has displayed.

08:26.702 --> 08:31.186
I have kept my heart laser focused on this.

08:31.746 --> 08:43.423
And when you keep your heart as Caleb kept his, I want to show you the powerful outcome, not just of getting what you believed for, but the kind of person you become.

08:43.463 --> 08:44.645
That's what this is all about.

08:45.346 --> 08:49.452
What does a last day's first responder in this nation?

08:49.873 --> 08:55.682
What does it look like to be fitted to our times in America right now as believers?

08:55.702 --> 08:57.324
So Joshua and Caleb are talking.

08:57.364 --> 09:01.330
He says in verse seven, Caleb states, I was 40 years old.

09:01.922 --> 09:07.007
When Moses, the servant of the Lord sent me from Kedish Barnia to spy out the land.

09:07.027 --> 09:08.328
He was one of 12 spies.

09:09.229 --> 09:12.072
He's talking to Joshua, who's one of those two.

09:13.853 --> 09:20.019
When he sent us out to spy out the land and I brought him word again, that was in my heart.

09:21.501 --> 09:26.786
But my brothers who went up with me made the heart of the people melt with fear.

09:27.827 --> 09:29.608
Yet I wholly followed the Lord my God.

09:29.628 --> 09:31.250
You see the power of leadership.

09:31.906 --> 09:46.770
This is why I think your pastors have excelled this year because when you hear your leader talk and when you and I talk, people listen and they're wondering what is the topic of our conversation.

09:46.790 --> 09:49.114
How are we describing the world that is around us?

09:50.056 --> 09:51.618
It has one of two effects on people.

09:51.678 --> 09:57.568
It causes their hearts to melt like wax with fear or it lifts their heart to new levels of faith.

09:58.309 --> 09:58.770
We're not.

09:59.042 --> 09:59.984
dumb in this room.

10:00.004 --> 10:07.055
We know we're in perilous difficult times, leading a Christian university in downtown Minneapolis.

10:07.115 --> 10:10.300
Are you kidding me in the last year and a half?

10:11.402 --> 10:23.822
We all realize what's happening in our world, not just in our city with the physical unrest, but with the madness of vain philosophy that is ripping our country apart.

10:25.445 --> 10:26.066
And yet,

10:27.138 --> 10:35.188
I see a Caleb-like moment, not just for my own calling, but also I saw it displayed in your pastors.

10:35.228 --> 10:42.917
When they talk about their world, which I believe is getting bigger, not smaller, I don't think opportunity is closing.

10:42.957 --> 10:44.119
I think it's opening to us.

10:45.040 --> 10:51.047
And that mindset of Caleb and Joshua to see the future in a way that the other 10 could not.

10:51.708 --> 10:55.212
I think that's first of all why your pastors are brilliant leaders.

10:55.713 --> 10:56.754
When I hear them talk,

10:56.962 --> 11:01.808
about the future, it lifts my heart, it doesn't make my heart melt with fear.

11:02.529 --> 11:06.353
So the Bible says that Caleb goes, when I spoke, I spoke differently.

11:06.373 --> 11:11.540
I said, all that was in my heart, they caused the heart of the people to melt.

11:13.061 --> 11:21.051
He said, in Moses, then swore on that day, verse nine, surely the land on which your foot is trodden shall be an inheritance for you and your children forever.

11:21.912 --> 11:24.155
Because you have wholly followed the Lord my God.

11:24.415 --> 11:26.738
And now behold, Caleb says,

11:28.578 --> 11:29.920
I'm as strong today.

11:29.940 --> 11:32.583
The Lord has kept me alive.

11:33.083 --> 11:41.193
And he said these 45 years since the time that the Lord spoke the word to Moses while Israel walked in the wilderness and now behold, I'm 85 years old.

11:41.874 --> 11:44.477
I am still as strong today as I was in the day of Moses.

11:45.298 --> 11:49.603
My strength now is as my strength was then for war, for going out, for coming in.

11:50.384 --> 11:55.890
So now give me this hill country of which the Lord spoke on that day.

11:56.322 --> 12:03.070
For you heard on that day how the anacom, which are the giants, they were these eight foot Canaanite giants.

12:04.873 --> 12:07.196
The giants were there and they had fortified cities.

12:08.117 --> 12:09.278
Which means they weren't visiting.

12:09.438 --> 12:10.380
They were entrenched.

12:10.420 --> 12:11.181
They were embedded.

12:11.221 --> 12:14.044
This was now their land that they had conquered.

12:16.287 --> 12:20.793
It may be that the Lord will be with me, Caleb said, and I'll drive them out as the Lord said.

12:20.813 --> 12:25.138
Then Joshua blessed him and gave him Hebron.

12:26.050 --> 12:28.794
He gave it to Caleb as an inheritance.

12:29.816 --> 12:35.664
Therefore, Hebron became the inheritance of Caleb to this day because he holy followed the Lord, the God of Israel.

12:36.065 --> 12:38.408
Now, there's this little throwaway line at the end of the text.

12:38.449 --> 12:39.350
People overlook this.

12:40.391 --> 12:43.556
Now, the name of Hebron formally was Kiryath Arba.

12:44.037 --> 12:47.061
Arba was the greatest man among the anacom.

12:47.502 --> 12:49.765
And then the land had rest for more so.

12:50.006 --> 12:55.474
Arba, this character that's introduced at the end of the text, he's the head giant.

12:55.714 --> 12:59.280
Literally, he's the nine footer among the eight footers.

13:00.382 --> 13:09.938
So the Anacom were very large, ominous, powerful conquerors of the land instruments of the enemy.

13:09.998 --> 13:11.341
Their leader was our Bob.

13:11.421 --> 13:12.863
We'll come back to that in just a minute.

13:13.845 --> 13:19.314
So Caleb is telling Joshua, I've been waiting 45 years for this.

13:20.098 --> 13:25.604
I literally have been looking out the window every day waiting for FedEx and UPS to deliver the package.

13:27.065 --> 13:28.907
Now, he said he's 85 years of age.

13:28.927 --> 13:32.411
He's aren't dog years or weird kind of Bible math.

13:32.451 --> 13:33.071
85 is 85.

13:34.413 --> 13:36.635
This was real 85, like our 85.

13:39.098 --> 13:40.119
Here's what's fascinating.

13:40.839 --> 13:47.346
Numbers chapter 14 tells us that at the beginning of the Exodus into the wilderness on their way to the promise,

13:47.778 --> 13:54.567
that there was so much negativity that the Lord said, all right, everybody over 20 is gonna die out here.

13:55.868 --> 14:00.094
You have no optimism in your heart, you have the spirit of the 10 that was afraid.

14:00.835 --> 14:04.680
If you're 20 and under, you're gonna live during these 40 years.

14:05.260 --> 14:06.402
Now let's just do the math.

14:07.123 --> 14:12.470
Caleb and Joshua were at least 40, that's what they say when they began their journey through the wilderness.

14:13.892 --> 14:15.794
They went those 40 years,

14:15.906 --> 14:21.531
There was a few years of settling, and now the escrow is being finalized, people were getting their territory.

14:22.372 --> 14:25.255
He said, now it's been 45 years, I'm 85.

14:25.675 --> 14:35.044
Which means that if you were 20, if you were the oldest person that made it through, 45 plus 20 puts you at 65 years of age.

14:36.085 --> 14:41.910
If you believe what the Bible is stating, and some scholars debate about LEESR, did this include the women?

14:42.671 --> 14:45.874
Most scholars, however, do believe that

14:46.242 --> 14:51.930
These were the only two 80-year-olds in the entire nation and that the oldest person would have been 65.

14:52.230 --> 14:55.895
Can you imagine an entire country and nobody's in their 70s?

14:57.578 --> 14:58.379
Nobody's 70.

14:59.120 --> 15:02.544
Two 85-year-olds and then the oldest next person is 65.

15:04.187 --> 15:07.331
So Caleb and Joshua are conversing in Caleb.

15:08.072 --> 15:12.498
Caleb looks at this opportunity through the eyes of faith.

15:13.826 --> 15:17.070
And Caleb said, I want the hills and I want the giants.

15:17.851 --> 15:18.693
I want the land.

15:18.813 --> 15:21.837
I've been waiting 45 years.

15:22.578 --> 15:26.123
Here's the first characteristic of a last day's first responder.

15:26.784 --> 15:28.286
It's God's plan for Caleb.

15:28.346 --> 15:29.808
It's God's plan for you and I.

15:30.629 --> 15:35.976
God's plan is for you to develop with time, not deteriorate with time.

15:37.118 --> 15:40.042
The reason this matters so much, let's be honest.

15:41.203 --> 15:43.186
We're watching our world deteriorate.

15:43.906 --> 15:48.372
And there's a natural space to getting older in which you kind of accumulate.

15:49.033 --> 15:54.361
I was going back through my yearbook from Bethany Bible College, the graduating class in 1984.

15:55.242 --> 15:57.305
The valedictorian is now an atheist.

15:58.066 --> 15:59.468
I said that person didn't make it.

15:59.508 --> 16:00.529
That person didn't make it.

16:00.570 --> 16:01.711
That person flamed out.

16:01.751 --> 16:02.472
They flamed out.

16:02.492 --> 16:03.213
They flamed out.

16:03.814 --> 16:06.578
It's not that everybody goes through a perfect

16:06.658 --> 16:09.741
upward linear straight life to success.

16:09.801 --> 16:16.068
We all go through valleys and trials, but I'm talking about people that are now shipwrecked in their faith.

16:16.088 --> 16:21.393
And you get to a point in life when you watch the world around you like Caleb watched his.

16:22.454 --> 16:23.535
How much can you take?

16:24.817 --> 16:33.906
How many dead bodies in the wilderness, his buddies, his friends, people that became negative and complained and lost their way or worshiped idols and they died?

16:35.586 --> 16:38.109
His whole world around him was deteriorating.

16:38.509 --> 16:42.814
You and I have to make one of the most important decisions of our life, I think right now.

16:43.735 --> 16:50.163
No matter what happens in my life, around my life, I should say, it's not gonna happen to my life.

16:50.323 --> 17:02.337
I might be the last Christian standing in my family, the last Christian standing in this office, but I'm not gonna let the deterioration of the world around me take away my development of my own face.

17:02.357 --> 17:03.538
Somebody say, man,

17:09.410 --> 17:18.441
God's plan is that we develop not deteriorate with time, that our faith becomes stronger, not weaker, that we become more, not less.

17:20.383 --> 17:28.113
We've gone through the kind of the socially, the fiery furnace, and I keep looking for the, when's the shelf life on this gonna run out?

17:29.054 --> 17:34.801
And I'm starting to wonder, is this the cycle until the return of Christ?

17:37.424 --> 17:38.866
But I don't want my faith

17:39.042 --> 17:42.266
to mimic this chaos that's going on around me.

17:43.167 --> 17:45.050
I wanna be like Caleb.

17:45.070 --> 17:45.931
I wanna be looking.

17:45.971 --> 17:47.994
Now how do you develop and not deteriorate with time?

17:48.014 --> 17:48.655
Very simple.

17:49.195 --> 17:54.062
You live in hope of the promise of God.

17:54.142 --> 17:57.446
I know it sounds very simple, simple theology.

17:57.466 --> 18:00.230
It has a powerful effect on your life.

18:00.270 --> 18:06.258
When Abraham lived in light of the promise of what God had given to him, it kept him

18:06.466 --> 18:10.370
Strong, it kept him focused, it kept him humble, it kept him repentive.

18:11.191 --> 18:15.596
We have to live looking out the window waiting for the package to arrive every day.

18:16.037 --> 18:28.110
When you read a promise in God's Word about your life, a promise for your family, a promise for this church, for this nation, every single day I'm living in hope of that promise to arrive.

18:28.410 --> 18:31.794
We've got many people that can't go four or five days.

18:32.770 --> 18:36.476
He went 45 years waiting for that thing to arrive.

18:37.397 --> 18:38.579
That's why he was stronger.

18:38.619 --> 18:41.363
Now, we all are going to get older, friends.

18:41.403 --> 18:41.764
Come on.

18:42.765 --> 18:46.030
I threw my back out the other day, chewing ice.

18:46.911 --> 18:47.192
What?

18:52.059 --> 18:58.789
I'm just slamming down in the morning some bareback and body, beat up, sore, can barely move, stiff.

18:59.290 --> 19:00.031
What did you do?

19:01.153 --> 19:02.034
I slept.

19:02.146 --> 19:02.947
That's all I did.

19:02.967 --> 19:07.915
I slept and I need bare back in body to get it going because I'm stiff and sorry.

19:07.935 --> 19:09.157
How many know what I'm talking about?

19:09.858 --> 19:10.039
Okay?

19:10.860 --> 19:17.010
There's some natural aging, but the outer man does not dictate my life.

19:17.090 --> 19:19.474
It's the inner man that's being renewed day by day.

19:19.915 --> 19:23.040
I clothed my outer man with my inner man.

19:24.122 --> 19:29.330
I don't let my outer man that's decaying day by day be the person that you meet.

19:29.922 --> 19:32.085
Be the person that responds to the challenge.

19:32.105 --> 19:39.356
I let the inner man that's being renewed day by day, that's the secret of Caleb because he looked in hope of the promise of God.

19:39.376 --> 19:48.850
When you read your Bible and God is delivering you this love letter filled with promises for your life, promises for your family, promises for the church, promises for the nation.

19:49.026 --> 19:52.169
We are all living in hope of those promises arriving.

19:52.209 --> 20:00.057
That's what keeps you vital, strong, and young because God's plan is that you develop with time, not deteriorate with time.

20:00.478 --> 20:05.943
Even though everything around you is falling in the wilderness, you're not falling in the wilderness.

20:05.963 --> 20:07.184
Can somebody say, amen.

20:07.445 --> 20:07.725
Amen.

